1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,160
{\an8}Greeting me with a bullet, huh, Khanin?

2
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:44,000
{\an8}It's the best way to greet an old boss.

3
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:47,480
{\an8}It's about damn time you took
responsibility for everything, Punlop.

4
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:48,960
{\an8}Pok, Prab, Pun.

5
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:52,080
{\an8}- You know this family?
- This kid is me.

6
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,320
{\an8}I'm the only son who survived.

7
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,320
{\an8}If we get it wrong two more times,
we're locked out for good.

8
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,200
{\an8}INSEETHONG FARM

9
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,720
{\an8}Maybe the answer lies in there.

10
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:38,280
Mine, in exchange.

11
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,120
Hey!

12
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,080
I'm deleting it.

13
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,760
So you're scared of me?

14
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:24,680
Looks like there's nothing left here
that's tied to the case.

15
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,640
What did you expect to find?

16
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,160
Whoever killed my real family.

17
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,440
I didn't want revenge.

18
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,200
I just wanted to reclaim my life.

19
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,520
Good morning.

20
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,640
Good morning.

21
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:04,560
Do you have plans for today? If not,

22
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:07,040
you're welcome to join
the barbecue at my house.

23
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,280
Listen, avoid using pesticides

24
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,560
or chemical fertilizers that boost growth

25
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,240
to make sure our consumers are safe.

26
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:34,880
If you run out of herbal pesticides,
we can always give you one.

27
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:35,960
Okay.

28
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:57,480
- Are they freshly picked?
- Yes.

29
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,560
- Ah, they look great.
- From the farm.

30
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,920
- This one too, right?
- Yes.

31
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,760
Your fever's gone.

32
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,160
Have you treated your wound?

33
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,120
I did it myself already.

34
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,480
Are you hungry?

35
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,360
Someone invited us to lunch.

36
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:10,120
It was Mr. Indhorn,
the son of the farm’s owner.

37
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,880
Welcome to Inseethong Farm,

38
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,440
Mr. Taiga, Ms. Rin.

39
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,200
Thank you.

40
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,720
It's so lovely here.

41
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,880
What about Mr. Narumit?

42
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,760
He's got to rest.

43
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:38,400
He can only walk outside
for a few hours each day.

44
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:42,680
Kids, feel free to come
get more anytime, okay?

45
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:44,800
Come on. Let's go.

46
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:50,520
And this is Piyanuch,

47
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,200
my dear mother.

48
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,240
Hello.

49
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:57,640
Hello.

50
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:02,920
After my dad was in a head-on car crash,

51
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:06,600
he was in a coma for a year.

52
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,560
He only just got well enough to come home.

53
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,840
Come on, honey. Let's not bring up
such serious topics with the guests.

54
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,880
Right? It's no fun, right?

55
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:21,840
Please, help yourselves. Dig in.

56
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:24,000
We made plenty of food.

57
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,080
Go ahead.

58
00:10:25,160 --> 00:10:27,320
So you two work in Bangkok?

59
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,360
Yes, we sell products.

60
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,000
{\an8}- Please dig in.
- Take it if you can!

61
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,040
{\an8}Give it to me!

62
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,200
- Give it!
- No way!

63
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:38,160
Give me that.

64
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,160
Are you okay?

65
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,320
Stop it! What's all this about?
Why are you fighting over it?

66
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,040
Wanna go inside, honey?

67
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,400
I'm fine, Mom.

68
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,960
Go get some rest, okay? Trust me.

69
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,160
Please excuse us.

70
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:14,560
Get some rest.

71
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,000
Everyone here is ill.

72
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,320
What's the map telling us to do?

73
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:51,560
Have you noticed anything strange?

74
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,400
Nothing related to 3C.

75
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,800
Mr. Taiga's work sure is interesting.

76
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,960
When are we getting our uniform?

77
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,000
I've been rushing him.

78
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,200
I hope it'll be done
before the Hi app's debut.

79
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,880
As if that could happen.

80
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,680
One minute he's working,
and the next he's gone.

81
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:34,280
- Techut!
- Hey.

82
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,440
Maybe he's got private matters.

83
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,960
We already found
a great designer, so why don't we

84
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:44,480
just be patient?

85
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:47,760
Some things take time.

86
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:50,880
Oh. Are you running a charity, Mom?

87
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,520
And here I thought 3C was a business.

88
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,720
It's true, I've never run
a business before.

89
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,520
Raising both of you has taken up

90
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,320
enough of my energy and brainpower.

91
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,560
Bring Taiga back to work.

92
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:17,120
He may be an artist,
but he's on our payroll.

93
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,560
He should learn to be responsible.

94
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:41,240
{\an8}I'D LIKE TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT OUR UNIFORM

95
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,840
- Let me take care of your wound.
- Don't.

96
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,840
Yes?

97
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:21,960
I was worried, so I came to check on you.

98
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,800
Someone was watching us.

99
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,520
Who? This place has security 24/7.

100
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:37,000
Has there been a problem
or a murder case at this farm?

101
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,840
Do you two know something?

102
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,560
I work at 3C.

103
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:50,240
Uncle Naruban…

104
00:18:57,360 --> 00:18:58,960
So he sent you two.

105
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:00,880
That's not it.

106
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:05,640
We've been uninvolved
with him for a while.

107
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:07,960
After my dad had a car accident,

108
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,680
Uncle Naruban cut ties with our family.

109
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,560
I used to be a policeman.

110
00:19:18,440 --> 00:19:21,640
But the accident changed my life.

111
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:33,480
I'm inside now. Our latest lead

112
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,520
is that he captured illegal workers here.

113
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,640
I found them. They aren't illegal workers.

114
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,520
They're kids. They're probably
selling them.

115
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,520
I'm saving them.

116
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,800
Don't be afraid.
I'm a cop. I'm here to help you.

117
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,720
I'll free you all.

118
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,480
Escape with your friends.

119
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:12,000
There are police waiting outside.

120
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:23,160
Go. Go!

121
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:27,760
Kid,

122
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,880
why are you still here?

123
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:49,840
Run as fast as you can.

124
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:53,920
Let's go.

125
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,000
Time's up.

126
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:12,520
Indhorn!

127
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,600
Indhorn! What's wrong?

128
00:21:16,720 --> 00:21:19,320
Tell me. What's wrong?

129
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,640
Indhorn. Tell me, honey.

130
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,840
Indhorn, what's wrong?

131
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:39,080
I've had an untreatable chronic headache,

132
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,920
so I had to quit being a police officer.

133
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:44,560
I couldn't keep my job and had to run
this farm instead of my dad.

134
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:51,920
Has your dad ever told you
about any cases at all?

135
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,160
Perhaps one about a family

136
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:59,240
where the parents and three children

137
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:01,960
were murdered ten years ago?

138
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,400
Let me take you back to your house.

139
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:18,480
That's alright.

140
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:22,880
My workers are waiting for me.

141
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,960
As for the case,

142
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:29,920
I'll ask my old workers for you.

143
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,760
You should watch the sunset.
It's so pretty. See?

144
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:57,040
There's a pretty view in front of me.

145
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,840
Why should I look elsewhere?

146
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:09,760
I'm not anyone's view.
I'm not pretty to anyone either.

147
00:23:17,760 --> 00:23:22,800
As humans, we tend to deny and deceive.

148
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:26,840
Maybe you met a bad person.

149
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:29,400
Maybe.

150
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:31,720
Until I found you.

151
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:35,640
I might be the most horrible person
you've ever met.

152
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,320
I'll wait till that day comes,

153
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,280
when you'll be
the most horrible toward me.

154
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,400
When I was little,
I was so afraid of the water.

155
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,880
My dad knew,

156
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:33,280
yet he threw me in the sea.

157
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:38,680
And so I could overcome the darkness,

158
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,840
the fear in my heart.

159
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:05,680
Don't make me turn on you here.

160
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:13,840
Horses like to eat fresh grass
because it's high in protein.

161
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,800
They can eat it frequently, even 24/7.

162
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,400
Twenty-four seven?

163
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:29,720
If they were humans,
they'd die from eating that much.

164
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:33,520
That's why they always get gassy.

165
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:42,240
Do you want them to relax
and train their muscles?

166
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:25,440
Get seated properly.

167
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:29,720
Or you'll break your back or a bone.
We're gonna be here for several more days.

168
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,560
Rin.

169
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,560
Can I

170
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:44,120
join you up there?

171
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:14,360
Boss, are you… Somebody help!

172
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,840
Boss, Boss!

173
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:20,920
Taiga!

174
00:31:22,960 --> 00:31:24,640
Mr. Naruban was poisoned.

175
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,280
We can't let this slide. Dad got poisoned.

176
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:34,200
God gave us a brain.

177
00:31:34,280 --> 00:31:36,120
Learn to use it, Techut.

178
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:39,240
If word gets out,
both our stocks and the 3C-Coin

179
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,640
will plummet.

180
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:44,520
You care about money more than your dad?
You ungrateful daughter!

181
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,240
If you're such a great son,

182
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,480
is that all you can think of?

183
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:51,240
If you're so smart,
why don't you tell me who poisoned him?

184
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:53,320
Think before you talk.

185
00:31:53,400 --> 00:31:56,120
If you act on impulse,
we're all going down.

186
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:59,000
Stop! Listen to me.

187
00:32:00,760 --> 00:32:03,800
Don't let anyone know your dad is sick.

188
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:09,280
He's just hospitalized
because he had a heart attack

189
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:12,760
and the doctor wanted him
to rest and recover here.

190
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:16,760
Who would buy that?

191
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:20,800
Who wouldn't buy it?

192
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:27,360
Convince everyone
that that's the case, okay?

193
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:48,600
DR. THANADOL SRISATHUWAT
NARUBAN ASAWAWONG

194
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:08,880
Don't think you can do anything
because Mom always backs you up.

195
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,639
Even if Dad becomes a vegetable
for ten or 20 years,

196
00:34:13,639 --> 00:34:16,320
3C will never fall into your hands.

197
00:34:20,679 --> 00:34:22,320
Looks like I'm not the one

198
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:25,199
who's the ungrateful child.

199
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:08,360
You've been through a lot, Naruban.

200
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:15,200
Soon, your duty will be over,

201
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:17,640
and you'll take a long break

202
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,360
with no more worries.

203
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:26,960
Mr. Taiga.

204
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:38,160
How's Mr. Naruban doing?

205
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:43,520
Leave.

206
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,000
Don't blame her.

207
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,680
I took her out to handle something.

208
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:52,880
And it's more important
than your work at 3C?

209
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:53,840
It was.

210
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,080
May I go see Mr. Naruban?

211
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,600
Sure.

212
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:40,840
I'm sure he knows

213
00:36:42,080 --> 00:36:43,160
how worried you are.

214
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:54,680
- Hello.
- Hello.

215
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,360
Thank you for coming.

216
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:00,880
Mr. Naruban's doing better now.

217
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,600
A tough man like him

218
00:37:02,680 --> 00:37:04,360
won't go down so easily.

219
00:37:48,680 --> 00:37:50,040
Where's my souvenir?

220
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,640
Next time, okay?

221
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:54,760
I'm mad.

222
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:59,520
Just kidding. Go get some rest.

223
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:26,040
Rin, come look at this.

224
00:38:30,760 --> 00:38:31,960
What's that?

225
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,240
There's one on this shoe too.

226
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:13,000
You don't need to put a tracker on me.

227
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,680
You sent someone
to follow me to the farm, didn't you?

228
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:17,000
I had to, Rin,

229
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:20,680
because if something happens to you
while you're with Taiga,

230
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:22,680
I should know first.

231
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:29,320
I'd do anything to protect you

232
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:34,120
because I've entrusted you
with watching over Mr. Naruban,

233
00:39:34,680 --> 00:39:36,240
the keyman of Fire Phoenix.

234
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:42,360
Although something bad happened to him

235
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:45,600
while you're with Taiga…

236
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:49,960
Hurry and find out who poisoned him.

237
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:51,680
Think.

238
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:55,440
Look deeper. Who'd benefit
the most from it?

239
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:14,240
Currently, 3C Group has taken
a few hits to its reputation,

240
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:16,520
which directly affects our credibility.

241
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:23,520
I’d like your approval
to fast-track the Hi app launch

242
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:27,520
and for me to lead 3C Group
into its next generation.

243
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:35,360
You called an executive meeting
without me?

244
00:40:36,040 --> 00:40:38,040
Techut, they're all senior executives.

245
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:42,160
Well, as a senior, do you ever care
about a junior like me?

246
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:46,680
Techut, apologize to them now.

247
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:48,200
Now.

248
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,120
Techut! Techut!

249
00:40:58,200 --> 00:41:00,960
- Techut, let go of me!
- Mr. Techut!

250
00:41:01,040 --> 00:41:02,160
Let go of her, Mr. Techut.

251
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:05,560
That hurts! Techut!

252
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:12,080
I'm alright. Thank you, sir.

253
00:41:13,760 --> 00:41:16,120
I'd like to apologize
on my brother's behalf.

254
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:18,200
I'm really sorry.

255
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:22,640
Should I call an ambulance
or arrange for your funeral?

256
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:41,960
So, let's continue
with our meeting, shall we?

257
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:51,080
What'd you get from Mr. Narumit's farm?

258
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:55,320
Everything surrounding Rin is suspicious,

259
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,520
but there's no evidence at all.

260
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:02,600
Could it be that love's blinding you?

261
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:08,960
Okay, maybe it's not love.

262
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:12,160
Maybe it's empathy,

263
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:14,240
sympathy, or intimacy.

264
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:16,240
They can all blind you.

265
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:20,240
They're emotions.
They're not facts or data.

266
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:25,160
You're an artist, so you're sensitive
when it comes to emotions.

267
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:28,520
If your opponent knows
that is your weakness,

268
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,400
they might take advantage of it.

269
00:42:31,640 --> 00:42:33,040
I know what I'm doing.

270
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,840
Just zip it.

271
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:39,920
No one would admit they've fallen

272
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:42,240
for a girl's charms anyway.

273
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:48,040
I'm not blaming you, I'm just saying.

274
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:54,040
Either way, the one
we should worry about the most is--

275
00:42:54,120 --> 00:42:55,000
Rin.

276
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:13,720
I'm sure you're aware of your misconduct.

277
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,360
Not coming in due to personal matters,

278
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:18,520
neglecting my dad during your work hours.

279
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:20,440
We won't compensate you a single baht.

280
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:22,680
We can even sue you.

281
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,000
What will you do first?

282
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:31,080
Are you firing, suing, or killing me?

283
00:43:32,520 --> 00:43:33,640
That'd be a waste.

284
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:38,480
But you've done it before.
Firing me because you're scared.

285
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:41,200
Watch your mouth. No one can help you now.

286
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:56,320
If you hate me, fire me.
Don't act like a spoiled brat.

287
00:43:57,960 --> 00:44:01,200
I bet no one's dared to tell you
how obnoxious that is.

288
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:07,200
Damn you, Rin!

289
00:44:09,840 --> 00:44:12,240
{\an8}<i>I want to talk to her in private.</i>

290
00:44:13,120 --> 00:44:14,160
{\an8}Nun!

291
00:44:14,240 --> 00:44:15,360
{\an8}He's not my brother.

292
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:17,520
{\an8}<i>He's just the troublemaker of our family.</i>

293
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:20,160
{\an8}<i>Khanin is one of Fire Phoenix' members…</i>

294
00:44:21,480 --> 00:44:22,840
{\an8}…just like Naruban.

295
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:23,880
{\an8}<i>The one who has to die…</i>

296
00:44:25,760 --> 00:44:26,800
{\an8}…is Taiga.

297
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:29,080
{\an8}Death is so close to us.

298
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:31,800
{\an8}So close that sometimes
we forget to watch out

299
00:44:31,880 --> 00:44:33,880
{\an8}which direction
we're getting stabbed from.

300
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:07,880
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

